<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/articles/articles.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Getting High on Weed<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.43)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=9034'>David "Turambar" F</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=9034&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> February 1, 2002</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> Just dropping a quick article here, on perhaps not the best way to play a fellowship, but definitely a very fun way.<br>
<br>
*Please note that this article does not advocate smoking or drugs.*<br>
<br>
Definitions<br>
<br>
PIPEWEED<br>
Top-quality weed from the Southfarthing, guaranteed to get you high in ecstacy. With pipeweed, relieve stress and burdens and feel the world get safer, as you share a tale and, uh, heal yourself. Smoke Old Toby, the top brand, or smoke Longbottom Leaf if you crave for heart disease.<br>
<br>
PIPES<br>
Comes in 4 different makes, each stolen and carefully duplicated from the original pipe, which belonged to these chain-smokers: Gandalf, The Gaffer, Bilbo and Aragorn.<br>
<br>
Function of a pipe deck:<br>
Get all 4 different unique pipes out quickly, with a couple of Old Toby&#39;s. In this situation, you can heal if the fellowship is bogged down by wounds and exertions with Aragorn&#39;s (keep in mind heal X companions, not heal X times), remove burdens which can be problematic against Sauron and Isengard (Gandalf), remove twilight after playing a lot of cards (Gaffer), or have some recovery (Bilbo), all by discarding (smoking) a pipeweed possession from the support area. Provides late-game support, and is most effective with large/varied/Gandalf-tailored fellowship.<br>
<br>
Making a pipe deck:<br>
<br>
1. Buy weed<br>
<br>
Go to your nearest local retailer, convicted druggie or black market sale and snap up copies of Old Toby, the finest there is, or if you&#39;re really addicted to smoking, Longbottom Leaf (not as effective) too. Don&#39;t forget to get all 4 different pipes unless you plan to turn over a new leaf and leave your weed on the table untouched. 2 of each pipe is usually fine for every deck.<br>
<br>
2. Stick it in your pipe<br>
<br>
Stick it in your deck. Do remember though that pipes are card-intensive, and would therefore work well with a Moria cycling deck.<br>
<br>
A pipe deck must almost always contain Gandalf to use Gandalf&#39;s Pipe (always use all four pipes to attain the highest value for X). Gandalf...an automatic choice would be Gandalf Friend of the Shirefolk due to the mediocre text of Gandalf the Grey Wizard. Therefore, play with all four races to maximise Gandalf (which is a complement since you need Hobbits and Men at least to carry 3 of the pipes).<br>
<br>
Of the 4 pipes, Gaffer&#39;s and Bilbo&#39;s can be played immediately, as you will always have at least one hobbit on the table. Playing a pipe on Frodo is wise, because you will never lose the pipe unless Frodo dies, which essentially means game over. The other pipe should be preferably played on Hobbit allies so that they cannot be touched by the enemy directly or easily except by Nazgul.<br>
<br>
The other 2 pipes are harder to get into play, needing their respective bearers to be on the table. Gandalf&#39;s Pipe can only be borne by Gandalf, Aragorn&#39;s by Boromir or Aragorn. Prancing Pony, multiple copies of the companions and A Wizard is Never Late can help out, and if there are problems, Gandalf&#39;s Cart can bear them for a while.<br>
<br>
The most important card in the pipe-cycle is Bilbo. You need pipeweed to smoke, and the more the merrier. Bilbo can cut down on the pipeweed you need, recycling your pipeweed after you smoke it, starting the endless cycle. One of the problems of recovery, that it slows down deck-cycling, is also unfounded with Old Toby as it immediately replaces itself in your hand, illusioned with the fact that you never drew it, but still got to play it.<br>
<br>
Bilbo&#39;s main strength is recycling Power According to His Stature. With this in mind, A few copies of PATHS won&#39;t hurt in a pipe deck (burden removable with Gandalf&#39;s Pipe). Elrond is also needed to heal Bilbo so that he can pick up those pipeweed from the trash can. And if you are playing with Elrond and Gandalf, might as well throw in Ottar to combo with Elrond and Old Toby&#39;s drawing ability (and card redundancy which can happen a lot with pipes) and Albert Dreary for protection against nasty conditions.<br>
<br>
Estimated Card-Slots Required: 20<br>
<br>
3. Proceed to get high and beat your opponent to a bloody pulp<br>
<br>
Throw Old Toby into the support area as soon as you get it. Slowly get the pipes out, then smoke, as the situation requires. Gaffer&#39;s pipe is an important factor in Twilight Denial (shameless advertisement of my other article) and can limit your opponent greatly, and is arguably the most efficient and perpetual pipe so far. Taking X as its maximum value of 4, smoking once or twice can quickly empty the twilight pool, making your opponent hard-pressed to attack. Bilbo&#39;s Pipe shuffles tales back, the notable ones including (have excluded cards like Last Alliance, Halls of My Home etc that are not normally in discard pile) There and Back Again, Saga of Elendil, Tale of Gil-Galad (people run at most 1 of each of Saga and Tale). Gandalf&#39;s Pipe late-game cuts down on burdens, which can be problematic against Enduring Evil, Ulaire Enquea etc. Aragorn&#39;s Pipe is also more inclined to late-game after the sanctuary of Site 6, its ability to heal usually 4 companions often simulating a sanctuary at the fellowship&#39;s site.<br>
<br>
